 Rose Water</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-ee03" data-pf-type="Section" id="Video" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-66_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-67_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-68_"><div data-pf-type="Youtube" class="sc-dAFaGQ gKtnlS pf-69_"><div style="position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;border-radius:inherit"><iframe class="pf-ifr" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hfdgRKanGho?start=0&autoplay=0&loop=0&mute=0&controls=0&enablejsapi=1" allowfullscreen="" width="560" height="315" allow="autoplay" title="yt-video" style="border-radius:inherit"></iframe></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6c5b" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-70_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-71_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-72_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_1000x.png?v=1711454056 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056 320w" width="3514" height="230" alt="Pflanzenstrich_blau.png__PID:b850d7e1-c00f-4273-9b83-e2ecbfbe7683" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-73_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-8941" data-pf-type="Section" id="RosaDamascena" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-74_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-75_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-76_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-77_ pf-heading-1-h3">Infused with Pure Sunlight</h2><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-79_ pf-heading-1-h3">Citrus essential oils are like captured summer days. Their scent is bright, clear, and alive–like a ray of sunshine reaching straight to the heart.
</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-81_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-82_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_falling_citrus.jpg?v=1771515857" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_falling_citrus.jpg?v=1771515857 1536w" width="1080" height="1500" alt="1080x1500 falling citrus.jpg__PID:1925bb9b-e336-4304-8fcc-915f4fbc10cb" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-83_ pf-image-1"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-84_ pf-heading-1-h3">Sun-Ripened  – Stored Light<br></h3><p class="sc-kUdmUV iejJTZ pf-86_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Citrus fruits mature on the tree for 6–12 months. During this time, they absorb many qualities of sunlight–from the intensity of summer heat to the softness of autumn rays. Few fruits store light energy over such an extended period. In the peel–gently cold-pressed to obtain the essential oil–this ripened year of sunlight condenses into fragrance.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-88_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_3citrus.jpg?v=1771515607" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_3citrus.jpg?v=1771515607 1536w" width="1080" height="1500" alt="1080x1500 3citrus.jpg__PID:02664a5c-713b-4b0c-8440-f0b10f830a16" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-89_ pf-image-1"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-90_ pf-heading-1-h3"> Forces of Light and Inner Radiance</h3><p class="sc-kUdmUV iejJTZ pf-92_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the anthroposophical view of Rudolf Steiner, solar, lunar, and stellar forces influence plant development and shape the formation of essential oils.Within the human being, these thermal energies are understood to resonate with the “thermal organism”– and, on a subtler level, with the inner self, the “inner light.”</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-94_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_foece_of_light_citrus.jpg?v=1771515629" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1500_foece_of_light_citrus.jpg?v=1771515629 1536w" width="1080" height="1500" alt="1080x1500 foece of light citrus.jpg__PID:e9f888fe-9f73-497b-82bd-4cd22fe869e5" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-95_ pf-image-1"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-96_ pf-heading-1-h3"> Solar Energy for Everyday Life</h3><p class="sc-kUdmUV iejJTZ pf-98_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Whether diffused in the morning, blended into a revitalizing body oil, or inhaled in moments of heaviness, citrus oils bring movement into stagnant moods and gently remind you of your own inner radiance.&nbsp;<br>Perhaps that is exactly what we need in darker times, a fragrance that reminds us light is always present. Sometimes hidden within a small fruit peel.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-100_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-101_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau.png?v=1711454056 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_1000x.png?v=1711454056 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/Pflanzenstrich_blau_500x.png?v=1711454056 320w" width="3514" height="230" alt="Pflanzenstrich_blau.png__PID:b850d7e1-c00f-4273-9b83-e2ecbfbe7683" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-102_ pf-image-1"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-113c" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-epRwmx cpmRjY pf-103_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-djVWQC dKziBg"><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-104_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"></div><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-105_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-106_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-107_ pf-heading-1-h3">Ripening Period of Citrus Fruits</h2><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cyRdfs qmQNK pf-109_ pf-heading-1-h3">Sunlight, Time &amp; the Truth About Color
</h2><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-111_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-112_"><p class="sc-kUdmUV iejJTZ pf-113_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Citrus ripening is influenced by species, variety, climate, and place of cultivation. Unlike climacteric fruits, citrus will not continue to sweeten after harvest — it must reach full maturity on the tree. There, under abundant sunlight and warmth, sugars develop, aromas intensify, and the peel’s essential oils reach their peak.&nbsp;Peel color, however, follows its own rules. </p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-115_"><p class="sc-kUdmUV iejJTZ pf-116_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">&nbsp;The familiar orange hue appears when cooler nighttime temperatures break down chlorophyll, revealing the golden carotenoid pigments beneath. In tropical regions, where nights remain warm, fully ripe fruit may stay green even when sweet and aromatic. In citrus, color is influenced by temperature, and maturity is defined by chemistry.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-tafSX ePbmtR pf-118_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:8px;--s-sm:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:3;--c-lg:3"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-pKreJ bIaXH pf-119_"><img alt="1080x1080 orange 2.png__PID:6770d1cc-1445-4484-a715-cff57105cab6" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1080_orange_2.png?v=1771848902&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1080_orange_2.png?v=1771848902&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1080_orange_2.png?v=1771848902&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0567/2563/5262/files/1080x1080_orange_